C1A-HS.processing: This signal is used for processing "AEB_VehicleAlertRequest2".

Simultaneously, "AEB_PedestrianAlertRequest2" in the same frame is checked.
If "AEB_PedestrianAlertRequest2" is 0b1 and if value is "0b00:No AEB vehicle alert", store 0b11.
If "AEB_PedestrianAlertRequest2" is 0b0 and if value is "0b00:No AEB vehicle alert", store 0b00.
If value is 0b01, store 0b10.
If value is 0b10, store 0b11.
If value is 0b11, store NULL

If value is 0b01 or value is 0b10, store 0b10.
If value is 0b00 or value is 0b11, store 0b00.

Apply following translation (from the value to C1A value)

from 0b0111 to 0b1111 is 111.

If "Vehicle/Received/Fuel/Consumption/TripUnit" value is 0b001, store the value in "Vehicle/Received/EcoNav/AverageDistanceForFuelEconomy" with an upper limit of 99.9.
if  "Vehicle/Received/Fuel/Consumption/TripUnit" value is not 0b001, store 0.

If value is 0b10, store 0b1.
If value is not 0b10, store 0b0.

Apply following translation (from the value to C1A value)
0b0 is identified as 1 in C1A
0b1 is 0
if any 4 bit group is in interval [10;15] instead of [0;9], put an invalid flag on the whole data

If value is 0b000, store 0b1
If value is 0b010, store 0b1
If value is 0b011, store 0b1
If value is 0b001, store 0b0
If any other value, it will be ignored.
